<subSubSection id="C33BFA85FF8AD930BE962C2CFE19810B" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="132" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9EA90EFF8AD931BE962C2CFCD287EA" blockId="10.[136,1452,263,2090]" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BE962C2CFE898672" bold="true" box="[189,315,1631,1657]" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Discussion</emphasis>
:—The prostrate habit of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BC642C13FCAA8672" box="[591,792,1631,1657]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humifusa">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BC642C13FCAA8672" box="[591,792,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Miconia humifusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at high elevation, only allies it to two other species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BB652C13FE458695" authority="Naudin (1850: 236)" authorityName="Naudin" authorityPageNumber="236" authorityYear="1850" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chionophila">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BB652C13FEBC8696" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Miconia chionophila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0D4FFFF8AD931BF3C2CF0FE458695" author="Naudin, C. V." box="[279,503,1667,1694]" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" pagination="83 - 246" refId="ref9577" refString="Naudin, C. V. (1850) Melastomacearum monographicae descriptiones. [series 3] Annales des Sciences Naturelles; Botanique 16: 83 - 246." type="journal article" year="1850">Naudin (1850: 236)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BFD42CF7FDB58695" box="[511,519,1668,1694]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">/</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BC3B2CF7FB1E8695" authority="(Don 1823: 311) Naudin (1850: 235)" authorityName="Naudin" authorityPageNumber="235" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Don" baseAuthorityPageNumber="311" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[528,1196,1667,1694]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BC3B2CF7FD498696" box="[528,763,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Miconia rotundifolia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0D4FFFF8AD931BD262CF7FC0A8695" author="Don, D." box="[781,952,1668,1694]" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" pagination="276 - 329" refId="ref8487" refString="Don, D. (1823) An illustration of the natural family of plants called Melastomaceae. Memoirs of the Wernerian Natural History Society 4: 276 - 329." type="journal article" year="1823">Don 1823: 311</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0D4FFFF8AD931BDE22CF0FB1E8695" author="Naudin, C. V." box="[969,1196,1667,1694]" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" pagination="83 - 246" refId="ref9577" refString="Naudin, C. V. (1850) Melastomacearum monographicae descriptiones. [series 3] Annales des Sciences Naturelles; Botanique 16: 83 - 246." type="journal article" year="1850">Naudin (1850: 235)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BA922CF7FE8786CA" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BA922CF7FA2D8696" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Don" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[1209,1439,1667,1693]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">Miconia rotundifolia</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BEA32CDBFE8786CA" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" box="[136,309,1703,1729]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chionophila">M. chionophila</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
constitute a species complex (or complex species). Though this species complex is morphologically quite variable in leaf shape and size, the leaf size of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BCFC2CBFFCD686EE" box="[727,868,1739,1765]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humifusa">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BCFC2CBFFCD686EE" box="[727,868,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">M. humifusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="4CD904EBFF8AD931BD582CBFFC6F86ED" box="[883,989,1740,1766]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" unit="cm" value="2.65" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="2.0">2–3.3 cm</quantity>
long) extends beyond the leaf size range of the aforementioned species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BFC82C83FD798702" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Don" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[483,715,1775,1801]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BFC82C83FD798702" box="[483,715,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Miconia rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rarely exceeds 
<quantity id="4CD904EBFF8AD931BD532C83FC1D8701" box="[888,943,1776,1802]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
long, often with a cordate base. The leaf size, combined with the petiole length that is at least as long as the leaf lamina, long internodes and conspicuous production of adventitious roots, allows 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BFF02D4BFD1B875A" box="[475,681,1847,1873]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humifusa">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BFF02D4BFD1B875A" box="[475,681,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Miconia humifusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be differentiated from other Andean prostrate 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BAC72D4BFA1E875A" box="[1260,1452,1847,1873]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BAC72D4BFAFB875A" box="[1260,1353,1848,1873]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Miconia</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Outside of the Andes, another specimen of prostrate 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BCE42D2FFC9E877E" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityYear="1794" box="[719,812,1884,1909]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BCE42D2FFC9E877E" box="[719,812,1884,1909]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Miconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with leaves exceeding 
<quantity id="4CD904EBFF8AD931BA052D2FFBD6877D" box="[1070,1124,1884,1910]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
long has been collected from the Talamanca mountains of Central America (
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BC882D0CFCFC8792" box="[675,846,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Davidse 25967</emphasis>
, NY), and is determined as 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BAB32DF3FAF68792" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Don" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[1176,1348,1919,1945]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BAB32DF3FAF68792" box="[1176,1348,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">M. rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Though morphologically quite similar, we hesitate to combine these disparate populations into one species. The Talamanca populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BF1B2DBBFE6887EA" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Don" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[304,474,1991,2017]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BF1B2DBBFE6887EA" box="[304,474,1991,2017]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">M. rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
need to be studied in closer detail.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EA90EFF8AD930BE962D9FFE19810B" blockId="10.[136,1452,263,2090]" lastBlockId="11.[136,1452,158,257]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="132" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">
One notable character of 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BFFF2D9FFD2D880E" box="[468,671,2027,2053]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humifusa">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BFFF2D9FFD2D880E" box="[468,671,2027,2053]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Miconia humifusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the yellow or purple hue of the leaves when dry. The closely-related species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BEC32263FE638822" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Don" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[232,465,2063,2089]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BEC32263FE638822" box="[232,465,2063,2089]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Miconia rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see also 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BC69227CFCA28822" box="[578,784,2063,2089]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Melastoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repens">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BC69227CFCA28822" box="[578,784,2063,2089]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Melastoma repens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nom. herb./ 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8AD931BD8B227CFB8D8822" box="[928,1087,2063,2089]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repens">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8AD931BD8B227CFB8D8822" box="[928,1087,2063,2089]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="131">Rhexia repens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nom. herb.) has been noted as a source of yellow dye called “ola-ola”, producing a yellow tincture, when combined with 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8BD930BAAA2AECFF0980D7" authority="Triana (1871: 127)" authorityName="Triana" authorityPageNumber="127" authorityYear="1871" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tiri">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8BD930BAAA2AECFABB80B3" box="[1153,1289,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="132">Miconia tiri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0D4FFFF8BD930BB392AEDFF0980D7" author="Triana, J." pageId="11" pageNumber="132" pagination="1 - 188" refId="ref10013" refString="Triana, J. (1871) Les Melastomacees. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London 28: 1 - 188. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1871. tb 00222. x" type="journal article" year="1871">Triana (1871: 127)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see also 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8BD930BF022AB0FE7980D7" box="[297,459,195,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tiri" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="11" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8BD930BF022AB0FE7980D7" box="[297,459,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="132">Tiri tomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nom. herb.) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C21D28DFF8BD930BCA32AB0FBD280D6" authority="Linneaus (1753: 505)" authorityName="Linneaus" authorityPageNumber="505" authorityYear="1753" box="[648,1120,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Papaveraceae" genus="Bocconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="11" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis id="B955751CFF8BD930BCA32AB0FCD880D7" box="[648,874,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="132">Bocconia frutescens</emphasis>
Linneaus (1753: 505)
</taxonomicName>
to dye wool (Ruíz annotation on MA sheet; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB0D4FFFF8BD930BF0D2A95FE2C810B" author="Ruiz, H. &amp; Barreiro, A. &amp; Dahlgren, B. E." box="[294,414,230,256]" pageId="11" pageNumber="132" refId="ref9846" refString="Ruiz, H., Barreiro, A., &amp; Dahlgren, B. E. (1940) Travels of Ruiz, Pavoin, and Dombey in Peru and Chile (1777 - 1788). Field Museum of Natural History, Chicago, 372 pp. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 2305" type="book" year="1940">Ruiz 1940</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
